---
name: scljet-sql-right-full-join
description: SclJet RIGHT and FULL [OUTER] JOIN (2 tables); matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet RIGHT / FULL join

`RIGHT [OUTER] JOIN` keeps every row of the right table (NULL-extended on the left where no left row
matches the ON); `FULL [OUTER] JOIN` keeps both sides' unmatched rows. `JoinSpec` gains a `rightOuter`
flag (`parseJoin` sets it for RIGHT, both flags for FULL); `joinExecute` adds a pass over the right
table emitting each unmatched right row with a NULL-sentinel left record — so `SELECT *` keeps the
left-then-right column order (unlike a table swap). Verified against reference sqlite3 (RIGHT explicit
+ `SELECT *`, FULL, COUNT), int==js.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, executeMutation, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t1", "CREATE TABLE t1(a INTEGER, x TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("p")), List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("q")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val d1 = apply(db0, "CREATE TABLE t2(b INTEGER, y TEXT)")
    val db = apply(d1, "INSERT INTO t2 VALUES (2,'m'),(3,'n')")
    show(db, "SELECT t1.a, t2.b, t2.y FROM t1 RIGHT JOIN t2 ON t1.a = t2.b ORDER BY t2.b")
    show(db, "SELECT * FROM t1 RIGHT JOIN t2 ON t1.a = t2.b ORDER BY t2.b")
    show(db, "SELECT t1.a, t2.b FROM t1 FULL JOIN t2 ON t1.a = t2.b ORDER BY t1.a, t2.b")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t1 RIGHT JOIN t2 ON t1.a = t2.b")
```
